"p2\">**</bpt>ListViewItem<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept><ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/br242919)</ept> or <bpt id=\"p3\">[</bpt><bpt id=\"p4\">**</bpt>GridViewItem<ept id=\"p4\">**</ept><ept id=\"p3\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/hh738501)</ept> control template, then review it in light of the above changes.","pos":[29708,29949]},{"content":"We recommend that you start over by editing a copy of the new default template and re-applying your customization to that.","pos":[29950,30072]},{"content":"If, for whatever reason, you can't do that and you need to edit your existing template, then here is some general guidance around how you might go about doing that.","pos":[30073,30237]},{"content":"Add the new MultiSelectStates visual state group.","pos":[30243,30292]},{"content":"Add the new MultiSelectDisabled visual state.","pos":[30297,30342]},{"content":"Add the new MultiSelectEnabled visual state.","pos":[30347,30391]},{"content":"Add the new DisabledStates visual state group.","pos":[30396,30442]},{"content":"Add the new Enabled visual state.","pos":[30447,30480]},{"content":"In the CommonStates visual state group, remove the PointerOverPressed visual state.","pos":[30485,30568]},{"content":"Move the Disabled visual state to the DisabledStates visual state group.","pos":[30573,30645]},{"content":"Add the new PointerOverSelected visual state.","pos":[30650,30695]},{"content":"Add the new PressedSelected visual state.","pos":[30700,30741]},{"content":"Remove the SelectedHintStates visual state group.","pos":[30746,30795]},{"content":"In the SelectionStates visual state group, move the Selected visual state to the CommonStates visual state group.","pos":[30800,30913]},{"content":"Remove the entire SelectionStates visual state group.","pos":[30918,30971]},{"content":"Localization and globalization","pos":[30976,31006]},{"content":"You can re-use the Resources.resw files from your Universal 8.1 project in your UWP app project.","pos":[31008,31104]},{"content":"After copying the file over, add it to the project and set <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Build Action<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> to <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>PRIResource<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> and <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Copy to Output Directory<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept> to <bpt id=\"p4\">**</bpt>Do not copy<ept id=\"p4\">**</ept>.","pos":[31105,31252]},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>ResourceContext.QualifierValues<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept><ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/br206071)</ept> topic describes how to load device family-specific resources based on the device family resource selection factor.","pos":[31253,31467]},{"content":"Play To","pos":[31472,31479]},{"pos":[31481,31734],"content":"The APIs in the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Windows.Media.PlayTo<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept><ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/br207025)</ept> namespace are deprecated for Windows 10 apps in favor of the <bpt id=\"p3\">[</bpt><bpt id=\"p4\">**</bpt>Windows.Media.Casting<ept id=\"p4\">**</ept><ept id=\"p3\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/dn972568)</ept> APIs."},{"content":"Resource keys, and TextBlock style sizes","pos":[31739,31779]},{"content":"The design language has evolved for Windows 10 and consequently certain system styles have changed.","pos":[31781,31880]},{"content":"In some cases, you will want to revisit the visual designs of your views so that they are in harmony with the style properties that have changed.","pos":[31881,32026]},{"content":"In other cases, resource keys are no longer supported.","pos":[32028,32082]},{"content":"The XAML markup editor in Visual Studio highlights references to resource keys that can't be resolved.","pos":[32083,32185]},{"content":"For example, the XAML markup editor will underline a reference to the style key <ph id=\"ph1\">`ListViewItemTextBlockStyle`</ph> with a red squiggle.","pos":[32186,32315]},{"content":"If that isn't corrected, then the app will immediately terminate when you try to deploy it to the emulator or device.","pos":[32316,32433]},{"content":"So, it's important to attend to XAML markup correctness.","pos":[32434,32490]},{"content":"And you will find Visual Studio to be a great tool for catching such issues.","pos":[32491,32567]},{"content":"For keys that are still supported, changes in design language mean that properties set by some styles have changed.","pos":[32569,32684]},{"content":"For example, <ph id=\"ph1\">`TitleTextBlockStyle`</ph> sets <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>FontSize<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> to 14.667px in a Windows Store app and 18.14px in a Windows Phone Store app.","pos":[32685,32814]},{"content":"But, the same style sets <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>FontSize<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> to a much larger 24px in a Windows 10 app.","pos":[32815,32895]},{"content":"Review your designs and layouts and use the appropriate styles in the right places.","pos":[32896,32979]},{"content":"For more info, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Guidelines for fonts<ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/hh700394.aspx)</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Design UWP apps<ept id=\"p2\">](http://dev.windows.com/design)</ept>.","pos":[32980,33138]},{"content":"This is a full list of the keys that are no longer supported.","pos":[33140,33201]},{"content":"CheckBoxAndRadioButtonMinWidthSize","pos":[33207,33241]},{"content":"CheckBoxAndRadioButtonTextPaddingThickness","pos":[33246,33288]},{"content":"ComboBoxFlyoutListPlaceholderTextOpacity","pos":[33293,33333]},{"content":"ComboBoxFlyoutListPlaceholderTextThemeMargin","pos":[33338,33382]},{"content":"ComboBoxHighlightedBackgroundThemeBrush","pos":[33387,33426]},{"content":"ComboBoxHighlightedBorderThemeBrush","pos":[33431,33466]},{"content":"ComboBoxHighlightedForegroundThemeBrush","pos":[33471,33510]},{"content":"ComboBoxInlinePlaceholderTextForegroundThemeBrush","pos":[33515,33564]},{"content":"Com